[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "31979ace9e5b7bf02840e7443eaaa2659c16de473b533725da1751740f38f209"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has an opening hand, 14 points and five \Ss. But NORTH beat him to the punch, 
so he overcalls 1\S. 

WEST also has 14 points, she doesn't care too much for \Ss, but she has an 
excellent stopper in \Hs. 
She jumps to 2NT, inviting EAST to bid game.

Since EAST has several points more than he might have had, and no 6-card \S suit to rebid, 
he happily bids 3NT.}

